   "body" : "A snapshot contains the utxo set, including the out value. To activate the snapshot, the hash needs to be calculated. As a side-effect, the total amount in the snapshot is calculated (as the sum of all out values), but never used. Instead of running into an integer overflow in an unused result, don't calculate the result in the first place.\r\n\r\nOther code paths (using the active utxo set) can not run into an integer overflow, since the active utxo set is valid.\r\n\r\nFixes https://bugs.chromium.org/p/oss-fuzz/issues/detail?id=39716",
